  "text": "Cardiac and vascular function-Baseline/resting cardiovascular traits (SBP, DBP, HR, CI [cardiac index], and SVRI [systemic vascular resistance index]) were estimated in twins/ siblings non-invasively using the DynaPulse oscillometric device (PulseMetric, Vista, CA) as previously described [CITATION_1] . Flow parameters (CO, SVR) were normalized to body surface area, to yield CI and SVRI. The correspondence between DynaPulse and more traditional or invasive determinations of cardiac output and systemic vascular resistance have been documented recently [CITATION_2] .",
